1
00:00:02,435 --> 00:00:05,487
There is a line in "Hedwig" that goes like this.

2
00:00:05,487 --> 00:00:08,549
"It is clear that I must find my other half.

3
00:00:08,549 --> 00:00:12,227
I have to find my other half.

4
00:00:13,129 --> 00:00:15,531
What does this person look like?

5
00:00:15,531 --> 00:00:16,991
Are they identical to me?

6
00:00:16,991 --> 00:00:18,684
Or do they look the opposite from me?

7
00:00:18,684 --> 00:00:20,580
Does my other half have what I don't?"

8
00:00:20,580 --> 00:00:22,822
Wow, what a show.

9
00:00:22,822 --> 00:00:26,601
- Isn't it too much for a Liberal Arts class assignment?
- The movie "Hedwig"

10
00:00:26,601 --> 00:00:31,554
talks about human nature and its fundamental desires.

11
00:00:31,554 --> 00:00:37,592
- Is he having a pre-Halloween party by himself?
- How can we become our true selves?

12
00:00:37,622 --> 00:00:44,632
And in the end, is it possible to find your true self?

13
00:00:48,414 --> 00:00:49,874
Well done.

14
00:00:49,874 --> 00:00:53,210
Next, group number 8?

15
00:00:54,229 --> 00:00:57,623
Ji Hyun, you went through a lot.

16
00:00:57,623 --> 00:00:59,183
Are you okay now?

17
00:00:59,183 --> 00:01:03,018
Yes, Professor, thanks to you. Thank you.

18
00:01:03,018 --> 00:01:04,680
You're welcome.

19
00:01:10,378 --> 00:01:13,664
We will start our presentation.

20
00:01:13,664 --> 00:01:20,525
The movie we chose is director Park Chan Wook's 2006 work, "I'm a Cyborg, But That's OK."

21
00:01:20,525 --> 00:01:22,926
The art direction in the movie, "I'm a Cyborg, But That's OK"

22
00:01:22,926 --> 00:01:29,788
was done by director Ryu Seong Hee, who also worked on the team since the movie "Old Boy."

23
00:01:31,816 --> 00:01:34,994
Young Goon, who believes she is a cyborg in the movie,

24
00:01:34,994 --> 00:01:38,922
throws a question at herself.

25
00:01:39,616 --> 00:01:44,200
"I still don't know what my usage is.

26
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:46,463
Why was I created?"

27
00:01:46,463 --> 00:01:50,009
Through the portrayal of a colorful psychiatric hospital

28
00:01:50,009 --> 00:01:55,912
we can conclude that the message from the art director was the following:

29
00:01:57,984 --> 00:02:01,919
Psychiatric hospitals don't always have to be gloomy.

30
00:02:01,919 --> 00:02:05,232
It's okay to be colorful.

31
00:02:05,232 --> 00:02:09,011
Even if you are a cyborg, it's okay not to eat.

32
00:02:09,011 --> 00:02:13,436
Adam and Eve, who was created from Adam's rib,

33
00:02:13,436 --> 00:02:20,756
can both live the way they want to live.

34
00:02:25,745 --> 00:02:29,500
Thank you for listening.

35
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:34,103
Ji Hyun, you got into a big accident,

36
00:02:34,103 --> 00:02:36,564
but group 8 did well.

37
00:02:36,564 --> 00:02:40,701
That's all for today.

38
00:02:41,452 --> 00:02:42,745
Class dismissed.

39
00:02:42,745 --> 00:02:45,231
Thank you very much.

40
00:02:45,231 --> 00:02:47,983
You did well.

41
00:02:47,983 --> 00:02:49,502
Are you feeling okay?

42
00:02:49,502 --> 00:02:51,795
- Walk carefully.
- Stop it.

43
00:02:51,795 --> 00:02:54,398
One step at a time. Oh, my!

44
00:02:54,398 --> 00:02:55,750
What is it?

45
00:02:55,750 --> 00:02:59,252
Did you see my presentation? You saw what I did, right?

46
00:02:59,252 --> 00:03:02,038
You guys failed big time.

47
00:03:02,038 --> 00:03:06,969
You should walk straight to Itaewon in what you're wearing.

48
00:03:06,969 --> 00:03:10,581
I saw the Professor giving you a B minus.

49
00:03:10,581 --> 00:03:13,659
Who gets lower than 3.0 for an elective liberal arts class?

50
00:03:13,659 --> 00:03:15,227
I'm fine with it.

51
00:03:15,227 --> 00:03:19,247
It's okay to be a cyborg, and it's okay to get a B minus.

52
00:03:22,418 --> 00:03:24,152
Will you move?

53
00:03:25,346 --> 00:03:27,597
Hey, Ji Hyun.

54
00:03:27,597 --> 00:03:30,033
Will you eat with me, please?

55
00:03:30,793 --> 00:03:32,753
Enjoy it alone.

56
00:03:32,753 --> 00:03:34,889
Enjoy your meal all by yourself.

57
00:03:34,889 --> 00:03:35,865
Bon appetit.

58
00:03:35,865 --> 00:03:37,683
Hey, Kim Ji Hyun!

59
00:03:37,683 --> 00:03:40,377
Kim Ji Hyun, you've changed!

60
00:04:01,270 --> 00:04:06,370
<i>[Ji Sub Lim]</i>

61
00:04:06,370 --> 00:04:08,820
<i>[Jun Taek Oh]</i>

62
